BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:6LX3COskZOjE-DDfyeiAf
SUMMARY:Pratidhwani and Unexpected Productions Present Improv-Asana
DTSTAMP:20260413T010503Z
DTSTART:20260416T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:What happens when South Asian artistry meets Seattle’s longest-
	running improv tradition? Nobody knows. That’s the whole point. \\n\\n\\n\
	\n\\nOn Thursday\\\, April 16th\\\, 8:00 PM\\\, Pratidhwani and Unexpected
	 Productions are sharing a stage for the first and only time\\\, and you’r
	e not just watching. You’re part of it. \\nFor more than 20 years\\\, Prat
	idhwani has championed South Asian performing artists and built community 
	through the power of live performance. Since 1983\\\, Unexpected Productio
	ns has been turning audience suggestions into full-blown theatrical moment
	s. Together\\\, we’re bringing two distinct creative worlds into the same 
	room to see what sparks\\\, and\\\, given the talent involved\\\, there’s 
	going to be a lot of laughter. \\nAnasuya (Ana) Basu\\\, Anise Rau\\\, Gau
	ri Shringarpure\\\, Ronak Sharma\\\, Siddhant Sharma\\\, and Sumant Gupta 
	\\nDirected by Siddhant Sharma \\nYour suggestions\\\, your joy\\\, and yo
	ur ideas are the fuel. These artists will take whatever you throw at them 
	and turn it into something that will suprise everyone… and make you laugh 
	out loud while doing it!\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/pr
	atidhwani-and-unexpected-productions-present-improv-asana/\n\nFrom Unexpec
	ted Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/pratidhwani-and-unexpected-
	productions-present-improv-asana/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\\\, 1428 Post Alley at the Gum Wall in Pike
	 Place Market\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98101\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2tX4bJwxtlPN2f_Z5TiWc
SUMMARY:Loose Cannons 2026
DTSTAMP:20260413T010503Z
DTSTART:20260416T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:Loose Cannons is Seattle improv at its most unpredictable. Ever
	y performance at Unexpected Productions in Pike Place Market is a one-of-a
	-kind experience: exciting\\\, unexpected\\\, a little dangerous\\\, and a
	lways ridiculously fun. This is the show where anything can happen and usu
	ally does. \\nPart One: Part One: The night kicks off with a unique perfor
	mance\\\, setting the performers in a new format with special guest improv
	isers showcasing their signature style or a never-before-seen format. Your
	 suggestions fuel the fire\\\, and the improvisers will ignite the stage\\
	\, bringing your ideas to life. \\nPart Two: The second half launches from
	 a single audience suggestion\\\, setting the performers in motion. It mig
	ht start with a song\\\, a monologue\\\, or a rapid-fire group connection 
	game. Whatever emerges will inspire spontaneous stories\\\, surprising twi
	sts\\\, and big comedic swings. \\nLoose Cannons is fueled by audience ide
	as\\\, fearless performers\\\, and the thrill of not knowing what happens 
	next. You light the fuse. They run with it. What they create is entirely u
	p to you.\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/loose-cannons-202
	6/2026-04-16/\n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/loose-cannons-2026/2026-04-
	16/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\\\, 1428 Post Alley at the Gum Wall in Pike
	 Place Market\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98101\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
